    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "thanks. that's a good start. could you add a little more warmth to it though? like, maybe something that acknowledges how much we genuinely enjoyed meeting them, so it doesn't feel too robotic or cold? i want them to walk away feeling like they really made an impression even if it didn't work out this time.",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Subject: Your Application for the Senior Developer Position\n\nDear [Candidate's Name],\n\nI hope this message finds you well. I wanted to reach out personally to extend my gratitude for your interest in the Senior Developer position at our Austin-based company. We were truly impressed by your skills in system design and your seamless integration into our team culture. Your dedication and passion for software development are qualities we deeply admire.\n\nAfter careful consideration, we have decided to move forward with another candidate who has a bit more experience with our specific cloud stack. This decision was not easy, as we were very impressed with your abilities and potential. We believe that this choice will best align with our immediate needs and help us achieve our goals more effectively.\n\nI want to take a moment to acknowledge how much we enjoyed meeting you. Your enthusiasm and drive were truly infectious, and we genuinely appreciated the opportunity to learn more about your experiences and aspirations. It was a pleasure getting to know you and seeing how your unique perspective could have contributed to our team.\n\nWe understand that this news may be disappointing, and we want to assure you that this decision in no way reflects your capabilities or the value you could bring to our team. We genuinely appreciate the time and effort you invested in the application process,",
      "source": "target",
